---
import spotifyProjectImage from "./../../public/images/spotifyProject.png";
import { Image } from "astro:assets";
---

<div
  class="border-4 border-dark drop-shadow-4xl bg-projectCardBg flex flex-col md:flex-row"
>
  <div class="md:w-1/2 overflow-hidden min-h-[280px]">
    <Image
      class="w-full h-full object-cover object-top"
      src={spotifyProjectImage}
      alt="React Server Components"
    />
  </div>
  <div class="md:w-1/2 p-8 flex flex-col justify-between">
    <div>
      <p
        class="font-lightFont text-sm uppercase tracking-widest text-dark mb-2 border-b-2 border-dark pb-2"
      >
        Featured Post
      </p>
      <h2 class="font-black text-3xl md:text-4xl text-dark mt-4 mb-4">
        React Server Components — What Are They and Why Should You Care?
      </h2>
      <p class="font-lightFont text-lg text-dark">
        React turned 10 and keeps reinventing itself. Server Components are the
        latest paradigm shift — components that run exclusively on the server.
        Here's everything demystified.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="mt-6">
      <a
        href="/blog"
        class="inline-flex hover:translate-y-[-5px] drop-shadow-3xl bg-drawerBackground border-dark border-4 p-3 px-8 text-xl font-bold button-link-underline button-link-underline-black"
      >
        <span>Read more</span>
      </a>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
